commit.message:
Move the metadata into `pyproject.toml`
Dropped Python 2.7

Move the metadata into `setup.cfg`
Drop support of raw `distutils`.
Removed `requirements.txt`.

Remove installation dependency on six

  The python2 life cycle is over and we can give up support for python2. Therefore, we no longer need to rely on the six module.

Reformat a docstring

Black 20 formats docstrings now
Correct a typo in requests_file.py
Version 1.5.1
Add a couple more paths to gitignore
blacken
Python 2 bugfix
pytest on GitHub Actions

Switch the version to 1.5.0

This changeset adds a feature, so to keep things in line with semver
numbering, bump the minor number.

Update the author email.

Also remove the unused 'os' import, and reformat for style.
Add set_content_length flag to disable on demand setting Content-Length in response headers.

Delete the spec file

This file hasn't been updated in a while, pretty sure it's out of date.

commit.message: New release 1.4.3

Fix the classifiers list

I'm not sure why this was ever a tuple or if it was once supposed to be
a tuple but pypi complains about it now so change it.

Skip the permissions test when running as root.

Read attempts as root will not fail with EACCESS, so just skip the test
in that case.

Resolves #11

handle missing locale in tests

i do not know if it is fair to assume the ru_RU.UTF-8 locale will be available for tests.

if it is missing, just skip the test
New version 1.4.2

Update requests_file.py

Set resp.url because many existing codes use this attributes.

New version 1.4.1

The only change is to add a wheel distribution.

Release as a universal wheel

By releasing as a [Python wheel](http://pythonwheels.com/) as well as a source distribution, you can speed up end users installs. After merging this command, to release you just need to run `python setup.py clean sdist bdist_wheel upload`.

Switch to the new Fedora packaging guidelines.

Fedora maybe got the upgrade path breakage sorted out, so copy and paste
in the new dubious template.
Release 1.4

Handle files with a drive component.

Add handling for URLs with a drive component, including the old-style
Windows URLs that use a pipe as the drive separator
(e.g., file://C|/path/to/file).

Also fix the URLs used in the test cases to properly encode drives and
directory separators that are not /.

Resolves #2.

Skip the locale test on Windows.

Windows is not as likely to have different locales available, so this
test isn't worth the trouble there.
